      "job_name": "mlp_pytorch_experiments",
      "output_path": "/home/maiso/cbu/slurm/output/%x-%j.out"
    },
    "software_requirements": {
      "python": "version obtained from `python --version` command",
      "conda_environment": "pytorch",
      "python_script": "mlp_pytorch_experiments.py"
    }
  }
}
```

This script is designed to be run using the **Slurm** workload manager. It defines several resource requirements, such as time, memory, and number of nodes, as well as specific account and job name settings. 

The script also relies on a conda environment named "pytorch" and a Python script called "mlp_pytorch_experiments.py". The exact location of the Python script is determined from a configuration file (`paths.yaml`) within the repository. 

The script checks for the existence of the Python script and the correct conda environment before launching the Python script.
